  Status: Open

  A Sierpinski number is an odd number k for which k * 2^n + 1 is never prime, no matter what n you choose. It is known that 78557 is a Sierpinski number (it has a covering set). The problem is to prove it is the smallest one, by finding a prime of the form k * 2^n + 1 for each remaining candidate k.

